"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"19d1c506-72ed-4b7d-b66c-fb6506c3a021\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"refactoring-transcript-reads\",\"slug\":\"jolly-noodling-swing\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_017uLR9uQyMG1aMnrPJHrR2h\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01EB33xykjmtZYuJEDsFRF6J\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2/docs/plans/2026-03-04-transcript-parsing-replacement.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":63021,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"output_tokens\":94,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":63021,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYhP7YVJ5dHXishjB4cTF\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"6710af33-4c57-49ee-b7af-e839db9f529f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T04:08:00.496Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6710af33-4c57-49ee-b7af-e839db9f529f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"19d1c506-72ed-4b7d-b66c-fb6506c3a021\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"refactoring-transcript-reads\",\"slug\":\"jolly-noodling-swing\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01EB33xykjmtZYuJEDsFRF6J\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01EB33xykjmtZYuJEDsFRF6J\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T04:08:00.511Z\",\"uuid\":\"9f667524-b4e4-4fb4-89f4-7be242bc3013\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"6710af33-4c57-49ee-b7af-e839db9f529f\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2\",\"sessionId\":\"19d1c506-72ed-4b7d-b66c-fb6506c3a021\",\"version\":\"2.1.63\",\"gitBranch\":\"refactoring-transcript-reads\",\"slug\":\"jolly-noodling-swing\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01EB33xykjmtZYuJEDsFRF6J\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Replacing Transcript Parsing with Post-File-Edit Hooks\\n     2→\\n     3→## Background\\n     4→\\n     5→The CLI currently uses **transcript parsing** to determine which files an agent modified during a session. This works by reading the agent's transcript (JSONL/JSON) and extracting file paths from Write/Edit tool_use blocks.\\n     6→\\n     7→With the introduction of the `post-file-edit` hook (PR #583), we now have a **real-time** mechanism that tracks file edits as they happen, populating `state.FilesTouched` immediately on each Write/Edit tool call. This document maps every transcript-parsing call site and evaluates whether the post-file-edit hook can replace it.\\n     8→\\n     9→## Data Flow Overview\\n    10→\\n    11→There are currently **3 sources** that populate `FilesTouched`:\\n    12→\\n    13→| Source | When | Scope |\\n    14→|--------|------|-------|\\n    15→| **Post-file-edit hook** | Real-time, per tool call | Claude Code only (for now) |\\n    16→| **SaveStep / SaveTaskStep** | Turn boundary (Stop hook) | All agents via `mergeFilesTouched()` |\\n    17→| **Transcript parsing** | On-demand (hooks, condensation) | All agents via `TranscriptAnalyzer` |\\n    18→\\n    19→Priority: hook > SaveStep > transcript fallback. The hook makes transcript parsing redundant for agents that support it.\\n    20→\\n    21→---\\n    22→\\n    23→## The Two Concerns\\n    24→\\n    25→Transcript parsing currently serves **two orthogonal purposes** that are tangled together in the strategy code:\\n    26→\\n    27→1. **\\\"What files did the agent touch?\\\"** — File list extraction via `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()` / `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()`. Replaceable by the post-file-edit hook.\\n    28→\\n    29→2. **\\\"Has the agent done new work?\\\"** — Transcript growth detection via `GetTranscriptPosition()` comparing against `CheckpointTranscriptStart`. Agent-delegated (each agent implements `GetTranscriptPosition` on the `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface). NOT replaceable — file tracking alone can't distinguish \\\"new work this turn\\\" from \\\"carried-forward files from a previous turn.\\\"\\n    30→\\n    31→These two concerns are currently mixed across ~5 strategy-level functions. The key refactor is to **consolidate each concern behind a single method** so all call sites funnel through the same code path.\\n    32→\\n    33→### Proposed Unified Methods\\n    34→\\n    35→```go\\n    36→// resolveFilesTouched returns the file list for a session.\\n    37→// Prefers hook-populated state.FilesTouched, falls back to transcript extraction.\\n    38→// All call sites that need \\\"what files did the agent touch?\\\" should use this.\\n    39→//\\n    40→// Logic:\\n    41→//   1. If state.FilesTouched is non-empty → return it (populated by hook or SaveStep)\\n    42→//   2. Otherwise → fall back to extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript() using\\n    43→//      state.CheckpointTranscriptStart as the offset (files since last condensation)\\n    44→//\\n    45→// The offset is always state.CheckpointTranscriptStart — all current callers use this\\n    46→// same offset (Site 1 passes it explicitly, Sites 2 & 3 use it via the wrapper).\\n    47→// This means the method needs no offset parameter; it reads it from state internally.\\n    48→//\\n    49→// Internally calls PrepareTranscript() for agents that need it (e.g., OpenCode export)\\n    50→// before falling back to transcript extraction.\\n    51→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) resolveFilesTouched(ctx context.Context, state *SessionState) []string\\n    52→\\n    53→// hasNewTranscriptWork checks if the agent has done work since the last condensation.\\n    54→// Uses agent-delegated GetTranscriptPosition() — does NOT do file extraction.\\n    55→// All call sites that need \\\"has the agent done new work?\\\" should use this.\\n    56→//\\n    57→// Logic:\\n    58→//   1. Look up agent via state.AgentType\\n    59→//   2. If agent implements TranscriptPreparer AND session is ACTIVE →\\n    60→//      call PrepareTranscript() to ensure transcript is flushed to disk\\n    61→//   3. Call agent's GetTranscriptPosition(state.TranscriptPath)\\n    62→//   4. Return currentPos > state.CheckpointTranscriptStart\\n    63→//\\n    64→// Returns false if: no transcript path, unknown agent type, agent doesn't implement\\n    65→// TranscriptAnalyzer, or GetTranscriptPosition fails. Fail-open: callers treat false\\n    66→// as \\\"no new work detected\\\" which is the safe default (skips condensation).\\n    67→func (s *ManualCommitStrategy) hasNewTranscriptWork(ctx context.Context, state *SessionState) bool\\n    68→```\\n    69→\\n    70→This consolidation means:\\n    71→- Adding post-file-edit support to a new agent only requires the hook to populate `state.FilesTouched` — `resolveFilesTouched` handles the fallback automatically\\n    72→- Transcript growth detection stays cleanly separated and always uses the agent-delegated `GetTranscriptPosition()`\\n    73→- The existing tangle of `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript`, `extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript`, `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` collapses into implementation details of `resolveFilesTouched`\\n    74→\\n    75→---\\n    76→\\n    77→## Transcript Parsing Call Sites\\n    78→\\n    79→### Site 1: `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript()` — Condensation FilesTouched\\n    80→\\n    81→**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:539-544`\\n    82→\\n    83→```go\\n    84→if len(state.FilesTouched) > 0 {\\n    85→    data.FilesTouched = state.FilesTouched\\n    86→} else {\\n    87→    data.FilesTouched = s.extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript(ctx, state, state.CheckpointTranscriptStart)\\n    88→}\\n    89→```\\n    90→\\n    91→**When:** Mid-session commit where no shadow branch exists yet. The condensation pipeline needs to know which files the agent touched to write checkpoint metadata.\\n    92→\\n    93→**Concern:** File list extraction.\\n    94→\\n    95→**Can post-edit hook replace?** YES — if the hook is active, `state.FilesTouched` is already populated in real-time. The `else` branch (transcript fallback) only fires when `state.FilesTouched` is empty (legacy session or unsupported agent).\\n    96→\\n    97→**Refactor:** Replace with `data.FilesTouched = s.resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state)`.\\n    98→\\n    99→---\\n   100→\\n   101→### Site 2: PostCommit Carry-Forward — `filesTouchedBefore` extraction\\n   102→\\n   103→**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:902-906`\\n   104→\\n   105→```go\\n   106→filesTouchedBefore := make([]string, len(state.FilesTouched))\\n   107→copy(filesTouchedBefore, state.FilesTouched)\\n   108→if len(filesTouchedBefore) == 0 && state.Phase.IsActive() && state.TranscriptPath != \\\"\\\" {\\n   109→    filesTouchedBefore = s.extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(ctx, state)\\n   110→}\\n   111→```\\n   112→\\n   113→**When:** PostCommit hook. Before condensation, saves the current FilesTouched list so carry-forward can compute which files remain uncommitted after a partial `git add -p` / `git commit`.\\n   114→\\n   115→**Concern:** File list extraction.\\n   116→\\n   117→**Can post-edit hook replace?** YES — same as Site 1.\\n   118→\\n   119→**Refactor:** Replace with `filesTouchedBefore := s.resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state)`.\\n   120→\\n   121→---\\n   122→\\n   123→### Site 3: `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript()` — Mid-Session Work Detection\\n   124→\\n   125→**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:1320-1343`\\n   126→\\n   127→```go\\n   128→modifiedFiles, ok := s.extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript(ctx, state)\\n   129→if !ok || len(modifiedFiles) == 0 {\\n   130→    return false, nil\\n   131→}\\n   132→// Check overlap with staged files...\\n   133→```\\n   134→\\n   135→**When:** prepare-commit-msg and post-commit hooks, when no shadow branch exists. Determines whether the agent has done work mid-session (before Stop) that should trigger checkpoint creation.\\n   136→\\n   137→**Concern:** BOTH — transcript growth detection AND file list extraction (tangled).\\n   138→\\n   139→**Can post-edit hook replace?** PARTIALLY. The function does two things:\\n   140→1. Checks transcript growth (`currentPos > CheckpointTranscriptStart`) — keep\\n   141→2. Extracts file list for overlap check — replaceable\\n   142→\\n   143→**Refactor:** Split into:\\n   144→- `s.hasNewTranscriptWork(ctx, state)` for the growth check\\n   145→- `s.resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state)` for the file list (used in overlap check)\\n   146→\\n   147→The current `extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` returns `(files, ok)` where `!ok` means \\\"extraction failed\\\" (agent doesn't support it, no transcript, etc.). After the split, the equivalent is: if `!hasNewTranscriptWork()` → no new work, return false. If `hasNewTranscriptWork()` → get files via `resolveFilesTouched()`, then do overlap check. The `!ok` failure case maps to `hasNewTranscriptWork` returning false (same fail-open behavior).\\n   148→\\n   149→---\\n   150→\\n   151→### Site 4: `sessionHasNewContent()` — Shadow Branch Content Check\\n   152→\\n   153→**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:1177-1303`\\n   154→\\n   155→**When:** prepare-commit-msg and post-commit hooks. Checks if a session has new content worth condensing.\\n   156→\\n   157→**Concern:** Transcript growth detection (primarily). Multiple code paths:\\n   158→- **Shadow branch exists + transcript:** Compares transcript line count *from the shadow branch tree* vs `CheckpointTranscriptStart`. Not file extraction.\\n   159→- **Shadow branch exists + no transcript (carry-forward):** Checks `state.FilesTouched`. Already uses state.\\n   160→- **No shadow branch:** Falls back to `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript()` (Site 3).\\n   161→\\n   162→**Refactor:** Phase 0 does NOT change the shadow-branch code paths in this function. They read transcript line counts from the git tree (not the live file), so `hasNewTranscriptWork` (which reads the live file) is not a direct replacement. Only the no-shadow-branch fallback (Site 3) gets the split. The shadow-branch path could be unified later but is out of scope for Phase 0.\\n   163→\\n   164→---\\n   165→\\n   166→### Site 5: `SaveStep()` — Stop Hook File Extraction\\n   167→\\n   168→**File:** `lifecycle.go:233-267`\\n   169→\\n   170→```go\\n   171→if subagentExtractor, subOk := ag.(agent.SubagentAwareExtractor); subOk {\\n   172→    files, fileErr := subagentExtractor.ExtractAllModifiedFiles(transcriptData, transcriptOffset, subagentsDir)\\n   173→    modifiedFiles = files\\n   174→} else {\\n   175→    files, _, fileErr := analyzer.ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(transcriptRef, transcriptOffset)\\n   176→    modifiedFiles = files\\n   177→}\\n   178→```\\n   179→\\n   180→**When:** Stop hook (agent turn ends). Extracts modified files from the transcript to include in the checkpoint's `ModifiedFiles` field, which feeds into `mergeFilesTouched()`.\\n   181→\\n   182→**Concern:** File list extraction.\\n   183→\\n   184→**Can post-edit hook replace?** YES — `state.FilesTouched` already has the complete file list. The categorized git status lists (`ModifiedFiles`, `NewFiles`, `DeletedFiles`) from `DetectFileChanges()` remain unchanged — those are separate.\\n   185→\\n   186→**Refactor:** Phase 0 does NOT touch `lifecycle.go`. This site is in `lifecycle.go` (not strategy), so it can't call the strategy method directly. The transcript extraction here is redundant when the hook is active (mergeFilesTouched is additive — hook-populated state + transcript extraction = superset, no harm). Options for a future phase:\\n   187→- Pass `state.FilesTouched` into the lifecycle context so `SaveStep` can skip transcript extraction\\n   188→- Or: leave as-is permanently since the redundancy is harmless\\n   189→\\n   190→---\\n   191→\\n   192→### Site 6: `OnSubagentEnd()` — Task Checkpoint File Extraction\\n   193→\\n   194→**File:** `lifecycle.go:521-532`\\n   195→\\n   196→```go\\n   197→if files, _, fileErr := analyzer.ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(transcriptToScan, 0); fileErr != nil {\\n   198→    // ...\\n   199→} else {\\n   200→    modifiedFiles = files\\n   201→}\\n   202→```\\n   203→\\n   204→**When:** Subagent task completion. Extracts modified files from the subagent's transcript.\\n   205→\\n   206→**Concern:** File list extraction (subagent-scoped).\\n   207→\\n   208→**Can post-edit hook replace?** NO — subagent transcripts are separate files. The post-file-edit hook fires on the *parent* session. Task checkpoints need their own file list scoped to the subagent's work.\\n   209→\\n   210→**Action:** Keep. Consider future `tool_use_id`-scoped hook variant for subagents.\\n   211→\\n   212→---\\n   213→\\n   214→### Site 7: `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript()` — Core Implementation\\n   215→\\n   216→**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:1415-1500`\\n   217→\\n   218→This is the shared implementation used by Sites 1-3. It:\\n   219→1. Calls `PrepareTranscript()` for agents that need it (e.g., OpenCode `export`)\\n   220→2. For Claude Code: uses `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` (main + subagent transcripts)\\n   221→3. For other agents: uses `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()`\\n   222→4. Normalizes absolute paths to repo-relative\\n   223→\\n   224→**Concern:** File list extraction (the implementation).\\n   225→\\n   226→**Refactor:** Becomes the internal fallback inside `resolveFilesTouched`. Callers never call this directly — they go through `resolveFilesTouched` which checks `state.FilesTouched` first.\\n   227→\\n   228→---\\n   229→\\n   230→## Summary Table\\n   231→\\n   232→| # | Site | Concern | Phase 0? | Refactor |\\n   233→|---|------|---------|----------|----------|\\n   234→| 1 | `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript:543` | File list | YES | `resolveFilesTouched()` |\\n   235→| 2 | PostCommit `filesTouchedBefore:905` | File list | YES | `resolveFilesTouched()` |\\n   236→| 3 | `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript:1323` | Both (tangled) | YES | Split into `hasNewTranscriptWork()` + `resolveFilesTouched()` |\\n   237→| 4 | `sessionHasNewContent:1177` | Growth detection (shadow branch tree) | NO | Out of scope — reads from git tree, not live file |\\n   238→| 5 | `SaveStep():233` | File list | NO | Out of scope — in `lifecycle.go`, redundant but harmless |\\n   239→| 6 | `OnSubagentEnd():521` | File list (subagent) | NO | Out of scope — subagent-scoped, keep transcript parsing |\\n   240→| 7 | `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript:1415` | File list (impl) | YES | Becomes internal fallback of `resolveFilesTouched()` |\\n   241→\\n   242→---\\n   243→\\n   244→## Implementation Plan\\n   245→\\n   246→### Phase 0: Consolidate behind unified methods\\n   247→\\n   248→**Before** touching any agent hook support, refactor the strategy layer. Pure refactoring — no behavior change. All existing tests must pass.\\n   249→\\n   250→**Scope:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` and `strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` only. Does NOT touch `lifecycle.go` or any agent code.\\n   251→\\n   252→#### Step 1: Create `resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state) []string`\\n   253→\\n   254→- If `state.FilesTouched` is non-empty → return a copy (hook/SaveStep populated)\\n   255→- Otherwise → call `PrepareTranscript()` if needed, then fall back to `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript(ctx, state, state.CheckpointTranscriptStart)`\\n   256→- Offset is always `state.CheckpointTranscriptStart` (all current callers use this same offset)\\n   257→- Returns nil if both sources are empty\\n   258→- Replace call sites 1, 2, and the file-list half of 3\\n   259→\\n   260→#### Step 2: Create `hasNewTranscriptWork(ctx, state) bool`\\n   261→\\n   262→- If `state.TranscriptPath == \\\"\\\"` or `state.AgentType == \\\"\\\"` → return false\\n   263→- Look up agent via `agent.GetByAgentType(state.AgentType)`\\n   264→- If agent implements `TranscriptPreparer` AND `state.Phase.IsActive()` → call `PrepareTranscript(ctx, state.TranscriptPath)` (ensures transcript flushed to disk, e.g., OpenCode `export`)\\n   265→- If agent implements `TranscriptAnalyzer` → call `GetTranscriptPosition(state.TranscriptPath)`\\n   266→- Return `currentPos > state.CheckpointTranscriptStart`\\n   267→- Returns false on any error (fail-open: \\\"no new work\\\" is the safe default)\\n   268→- Replaces the growth-detection half of Site 3\\n   269→\\n   270→#### Step 3: Refactor `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript` (Site 3)\\n   271→\\n   272→Current logic:\\n   273→```\\n   274→extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript → (files, ok)\\n   275→if !ok || len(files) == 0 → return false\\n   276→check overlap with staged files → return result\\n   277→```\\n   278→\\n   279→New logic:\\n   280→```\\n   281→if !hasNewTranscriptWork(ctx, state) → return false\\n   282→files := resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state)\\n   283→if len(files) == 0 → return false\\n   284→check overlap with staged files → return result\\n   285→```\\n   286→\\n   287→The `!ok` failure case (agent doesn't support transcript analysis, no transcript path, etc.) maps to `hasNewTranscriptWork` returning false — same fail-open behavior.\\n   288→\\n   289→#### Step 4: Delete wrapper functions\\n   290→\\n   291→- `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript` → all callers now use `resolveFilesTouched`\\n   292→- `extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` → replaced by `hasNewTranscriptWork` + `resolveFilesTouched`\\n   293→- `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` → becomes private implementation detail of `resolveFilesTouched` (kept, but no longer called directly)\\n   294→\\n   295→#### What Phase 0 does NOT touch\\n   296→\\n   297→- `sessionHasNewContent()` (Site 4) — reads transcript lines from shadow branch git tree, not live file. Out of scope.\\n   298→- `SaveStep()` / `OnSubagentEnd()` (Sites 5, 6) — in `lifecycle.go`, not strategy. Out of scope.\\n   299→- Any agent code — no changes to `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface or implementations.\\n   300→- `PrepareTranscript` logic — moved into the two new methods but behavior is identical.\\n   301→\\n   302→### Phase 1: All agents support post-file-edit hook\\n   303→\\n   304→| Agent | Hook Support | Notes |\\n   305→|-------|-------------|-------|\\n   306→| Claude Code | YES (PR #583) | PostToolUse with Write/Edit matchers |\\n   307→| Gemini CLI | NO | Needs equivalent hook mechanism |\\n   308→| OpenCode | NO | Needs equivalent hook mechanism |\\n   309→| Cursor | NO | Needs equivalent hook mechanism |\\n   310→| Factory AI Droid | NO | Needs equivalent hook mechanism |\\n   311→\\n   312→Once all agents fire the hook, `resolveFilesTouched` will almost always take the fast path (`state.FilesTouched` non-empty). The transcript fallback becomes legacy-only.\\n   313→\\n   314→### Phase 2: Simplify `resolveFilesTouched` (optional)\\n   315→\\n   316→Once we're confident the hook covers all agents:\\n   317→\\n   318→1. Add agent capability check — if agent supports post-file-edit hook AND `state.FilesTouched` is empty, skip transcript parsing (no files touched = no files to report)\\n   319→2. Keep transcript fallback behind a flag or for agents that opt out\\n   320→3. `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` remains available for `OnSubagentEnd()` (Site 6)\\n   321→\\n   322→### Non-Goals\\n   323→\\n   324→- **Transcript growth detection** (`countTranscriptItems`, `GetTranscriptPosition`): NOT being replaced. These answer \\\"has the agent done new work?\\\" which is orthogonal to file tracking. Stays agent-delegated.\\n   325→- **Prompt extraction** (`extractUserPrompts`): NOT related to file tracking.\\n   326→- **Token usage calculation** (`CalculateTokenUsage`): NOT related to file tracking.\\n   327→- **Subagent file extraction** (`OnSubagentEnd`): Requires per-task scoping that the current hook doesn't provide.\\n   328→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"7dbca991-0fed-41f7-bc0f-c9b94dd1115e\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-04T04:08:00.510Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alex/workspace/cli/.worktrees/2/docs/plans/2026-03-04-transcript-parsing-replacement.md\",\"content\":\"# Replacing Transcript Parsing with Post-File-Edit Hooks\\n\\n## Background\\n\\nThe CLI currently uses **transcript parsing** to determine which files an agent modified during a session. This works by reading the agent's transcript (JSONL/JSON) and extracting file paths from Write/Edit tool_use blocks.\\n\\nWith the introduction of the `post-file-edit` hook (PR #583), we now have a **real-time** mechanism that tracks file edits as they happen, populating `state.FilesTouched` immediately on each Write/Edit tool call. This document maps every transcript-parsing call site and evaluates whether the post-file-edit hook can replace it.\\n\\n## Data Flow Overview\\n\\nThere are currently **3 sources** that populate `FilesTouched`:\\n\\n| Source | When | Scope |\\n|--------|------|-------|\\n| **Post-file-edit hook** | Real-time, per tool call | Claude Code only (for now) |\\n| **SaveStep / SaveTaskStep** | Turn boundary (Stop hook) | All agents via `mergeFilesTouched()` |\\n| **Transcript parsing** | On-demand (hooks, condensation) | All agents via `TranscriptAnalyzer` |\\n\\nPriority: hook > SaveStep > transcript fallback. The hook makes transcript parsing redundant for agents that support it.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## The Two Concerns\\n\\nTranscript parsing currently serves **two orthogonal purposes** that are tangled together in the strategy code:\\n\\n1. **\\\"What files did the agent touch?\\\"** — File list extraction via `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()` / `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()`. Replaceable by the post-file-edit hook.\\n\\n2. **\\\"Has the agent done new work?\\\"** — Transcript growth detection via `GetTranscriptPosition()` comparing against `CheckpointTranscriptStart`. Agent-delegated (each agent implements `GetTranscriptPosition` on the `TranscriptAnalyzer` interface). NOT replaceable — file tracking alone can't distinguish \\\"new work this turn\\\" from \\\"carried-forward files from a previous turn.\\\"\\n\\nThese two concerns are currently mixed across ~5 strategy-level functions. The key refactor is to **consolidate each concern behind a single method** so all call sites funnel through the same code path.\\n\\n### Proposed Unified Methods\\n\\n```go\\n// resolveFilesTouched returns the file list for a session.\\n// Prefers hook-populated state.FilesTouched, falls back to transcript extraction.\\n// All call sites that need \\\"what files did the agent touch?\\\" should use this.\\n//\\n// Logic:\\n//   1. If state.FilesTouched is non-empty → return it (populated by hook or SaveStep)\\n//   2. Otherwise → fall back to extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript() using\\n//      state.CheckpointTranscriptStart as the offset (files since last condensation)\\n//\\n// The offset is always state.CheckpointTranscriptStart — all current callers use this\\n// same offset (Site 1 passes it explicitly, Sites 2 & 3 use it via the wrapper).\\n// This means the method needs no offset parameter; it reads it from state internally.\\n//\\n// Internally calls PrepareTranscript() for agents that need it (e.g., OpenCode export)\\n// before falling back to transcript extraction.\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) resolveFilesTouched(ctx context.Context, state *SessionState) []string\\n\\n// hasNewTranscriptWork checks if the agent has done work since the last condensation.\\n// Uses agent-delegated GetTranscriptPosition() — does NOT do file extraction.\\n// All call sites that need \\\"has the agent done new work?\\\" should use this.\\n//\\n// Logic:\\n//   1. Look up agent via state.AgentType\\n//   2. If agent implements TranscriptPreparer AND session is ACTIVE →\\n//      call PrepareTranscript() to ensure transcript is flushed to disk\\n//   3. Call agent's GetTranscriptPosition(state.TranscriptPath)\\n//   4. Return currentPos > state.CheckpointTranscriptStart\\n//\\n// Returns false if: no transcript path, unknown agent type, agent doesn't implement\\n// TranscriptAnalyzer, or GetTranscriptPosition fails. Fail-open: callers treat false\\n// as \\\"no new work detected\\\" which is the safe default (skips condensation).\\nfunc (s *ManualCommitStrategy) hasNewTranscriptWork(ctx context.Context, state *SessionState) bool\\n```\\n\\nThis consolidation means:\\n- Adding post-file-edit support to a new agent only requires the hook to populate `state.FilesTouched` — `resolveFilesTouched` handles the fallback automatically\\n- Transcript growth detection stays cleanly separated and always uses the agent-delegated `GetTranscriptPosition()`\\n- The existing tangle of `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript`, `extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript`, `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` collapses into implementation details of `resolveFilesTouched`\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Transcript Parsing Call Sites\\n\\n### Site 1: `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript()` — Condensation FilesTouched\\n\\n**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go:539-544`\\n\\n```go\\nif len(state.FilesTouched) > 0 {\\n    data.FilesTouched = state.FilesTouched\\n} else {\\n    data.FilesTouched = s.extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript(ctx, state, state.CheckpointTranscriptStart)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**When:** Mid-session commit where no shadow branch exists yet. The condensation pipeline needs to know which files the agent touched to write checkpoint metadata.\\n\\n**Concern:** File list extraction.\\n\\n**Can post-edit hook replace?** YES — if the hook is active, `state.FilesTouched` is already populated in real-time. The `else` branch (transcript fallback) only fires when `state.FilesTouched` is empty (legacy session or unsupported agent).\\n\\n**Refactor:** Replace with `data.FilesTouched = s.resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state)`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Site 2: PostCommit Carry-Forward — `filesTouchedBefore` extraction\\n\\n**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:902-906`\\n\\n```go\\nfilesTouchedBefore := make([]string, len(state.FilesTouched))\\ncopy(filesTouchedBefore, state.FilesTouched)\\nif len(filesTouchedBefore) == 0 && state.Phase.IsActive() && state.TranscriptPath != \\\"\\\" {\\n    filesTouchedBefore = s.extractFilesFromLiveTranscript(ctx, state)\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**When:** PostCommit hook. Before condensation, saves the current FilesTouched list so carry-forward can compute which files remain uncommitted after a partial `git add -p` / `git commit`.\\n\\n**Concern:** File list extraction.\\n\\n**Can post-edit hook replace?** YES — same as Site 1.\\n\\n**Refactor:** Replace with `filesTouchedBefore := s.resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state)`.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Site 3: `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript()` — Mid-Session Work Detection\\n\\n**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:1320-1343`\\n\\n```go\\nmodifiedFiles, ok := s.extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript(ctx, state)\\nif !ok || len(modifiedFiles) == 0 {\\n    return false, nil\\n}\\n// Check overlap with staged files...\\n```\\n\\n**When:** prepare-commit-msg and post-commit hooks, when no shadow branch exists. Determines whether the agent has done work mid-session (before Stop) that should trigger checkpoint creation.\\n\\n**Concern:** BOTH — transcript growth detection AND file list extraction (tangled).\\n\\n**Can post-edit hook replace?** PARTIALLY. The function does two things:\\n1. Checks transcript growth (`currentPos > CheckpointTranscriptStart`) — keep\\n2. Extracts file list for overlap check — replaceable\\n\\n**Refactor:** Split into:\\n- `s.hasNewTranscriptWork(ctx, state)` for the growth check\\n- `s.resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state)` for the file list (used in overlap check)\\n\\nThe current `extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` returns `(files, ok)` where `!ok` means \\\"extraction failed\\\" (agent doesn't support it, no transcript, etc.). After the split, the equivalent is: if `!hasNewTranscriptWork()` → no new work, return false. If `hasNewTranscriptWork()` → get files via `resolveFilesTouched()`, then do overlap check. The `!ok` failure case maps to `hasNewTranscriptWork` returning false (same fail-open behavior).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Site 4: `sessionHasNewContent()` — Shadow Branch Content Check\\n\\n**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:1177-1303`\\n\\n**When:** prepare-commit-msg and post-commit hooks. Checks if a session has new content worth condensing.\\n\\n**Concern:** Transcript growth detection (primarily). Multiple code paths:\\n- **Shadow branch exists + transcript:** Compares transcript line count *from the shadow branch tree* vs `CheckpointTranscriptStart`. Not file extraction.\\n- **Shadow branch exists + no transcript (carry-forward):** Checks `state.FilesTouched`. Already uses state.\\n- **No shadow branch:** Falls back to `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript()` (Site 3).\\n\\n**Refactor:** Phase 0 does NOT change the shadow-branch code paths in this function. They read transcript line counts from the git tree (not the live file), so `hasNewTranscriptWork` (which reads the live file) is not a direct replacement. Only the no-shadow-branch fallback (Site 3) gets the split. The shadow-branch path could be unified later but is out of scope for Phase 0.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Site 5: `SaveStep()` — Stop Hook File Extraction\\n\\n**File:** `lifecycle.go:233-267`\\n\\n```go\\nif subagentExtractor, subOk := ag.(agent.SubagentAwareExtractor); subOk {\\n    files, fileErr := subagentExtractor.ExtractAllModifiedFiles(transcriptData, transcriptOffset, subagentsDir)\\n    modifiedFiles = files\\n} else {\\n    files, _, fileErr := analyzer.ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(transcriptRef, transcriptOffset)\\n    modifiedFiles = files\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**When:** Stop hook (agent turn ends). Extracts modified files from the transcript to include in the checkpoint's `ModifiedFiles` field, which feeds into `mergeFilesTouched()`.\\n\\n**Concern:** File list extraction.\\n\\n**Can post-edit hook replace?** YES — `state.FilesTouched` already has the complete file list. The categorized git status lists (`ModifiedFiles`, `NewFiles`, `DeletedFiles`) from `DetectFileChanges()` remain unchanged — those are separate.\\n\\n**Refactor:** Phase 0 does NOT touch `lifecycle.go`. This site is in `lifecycle.go` (not strategy), so it can't call the strategy method directly. The transcript extraction here is redundant when the hook is active (mergeFilesTouched is additive — hook-populated state + transcript extraction = superset, no harm). Options for a future phase:\\n- Pass `state.FilesTouched` into the lifecycle context so `SaveStep` can skip transcript extraction\\n- Or: leave as-is permanently since the redundancy is harmless\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Site 6: `OnSubagentEnd()` — Task Checkpoint File Extraction\\n\\n**File:** `lifecycle.go:521-532`\\n\\n```go\\nif files, _, fileErr := analyzer.ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset(transcriptToScan, 0); fileErr != nil {\\n    // ...\\n} else {\\n    modifiedFiles = files\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**When:** Subagent task completion. Extracts modified files from the subagent's transcript.\\n\\n**Concern:** File list extraction (subagent-scoped).\\n\\n**Can post-edit hook replace?** NO — subagent transcripts are separate files. The post-file-edit hook fires on the *parent* session. Task checkpoints need their own file list scoped to the subagent's work.\\n\\n**Action:** Keep. Consider future `tool_use_id`-scoped hook variant for subagents.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Site 7: `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript()` — Core Implementation\\n\\n**File:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go:1415-1500`\\n\\nThis is the shared implementation used by Sites 1-3. It:\\n1. Calls `PrepareTranscript()` for agents that need it (e.g., OpenCode `export`)\\n2. For Claude Code: uses `ExtractAllModifiedFiles()` (main + subagent transcripts)\\n3. For other agents: uses `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset()`\\n4. Normalizes absolute paths to repo-relative\\n\\n**Concern:** File list extraction (the implementation).\\n\\n**Refactor:** Becomes the internal fallback inside `resolveFilesTouched`. Callers never call this directly — they go through `resolveFilesTouched` which checks `state.FilesTouched` first.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Summary Table\\n\\n| # | Site | Concern | Phase 0? | Refactor |\\n|---|------|---------|----------|----------|\\n| 1 | `extractSessionDataFromLiveTranscript:543` | File list | YES | `resolveFilesTouched()` |\\n| 2 | PostCommit `filesTouchedBefore:905` | File list | YES | `resolveFilesTouched()` |\\n| 3 | `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript:1323` | Both (tangled) | YES | Split into `hasNewTranscriptWork()` + `resolveFilesTouched()` |\\n| 4 | `sessionHasNewContent:1177` | Growth detection (shadow branch tree) | NO | Out of scope — reads from git tree, not live file |\\n| 5 | `SaveStep():233` | File list | NO | Out of scope — in `lifecycle.go`, redundant but harmless |\\n| 6 | `OnSubagentEnd():521` | File list (subagent) | NO | Out of scope — subagent-scoped, keep transcript parsing |\\n| 7 | `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript:1415` | File list (impl) | YES | Becomes internal fallback of `resolveFilesTouched()` |\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Implementation Plan\\n\\n### Phase 0: Consolidate behind unified methods\\n\\n**Before** touching any agent hook support, refactor the strategy layer. Pure refactoring — no behavior change. All existing tests must pass.\\n\\n**Scope:** `strategy/manual_commit_hooks.go` and `strategy/manual_commit_condensation.go` only. Does NOT touch `lifecycle.go` or any agent code.\\n\\n#### Step 1: Create `resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state) []string`\\n\\n- If `state.FilesTouched` is non-empty → return a copy (hook/SaveStep populated)\\n- Otherwise → call `PrepareTranscript()` if needed, then fall back to `extractModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript(ctx, state, state.CheckpointTranscriptStart)`\\n- Offset is always `state.CheckpointTranscriptStart` (all current callers use this same offset)\\n- Returns nil if both sources are empty\\n- Replace call sites 1, 2, and the file-list half of 3\\n\\n#### Step 2: Create `hasNewTranscriptWork(ctx, state) bool`\\n\\n- If `state.TranscriptPath == \\\"\\\"` or `state.AgentType == \\\"\\\"` → return false\\n- Look up agent via `agent.GetByAgentType(state.AgentType)`\\n- If agent implements `TranscriptPreparer` AND `state.Phase.IsActive()` → call `PrepareTranscript(ctx, state.TranscriptPath)` (ensures transcript flushed to disk, e.g., OpenCode `export`)\\n- If agent implements `TranscriptAnalyzer` → call `GetTranscriptPosition(state.TranscriptPath)`\\n- Return `currentPos > state.CheckpointTranscriptStart`\\n- Returns false on any error (fail-open: \\\"no new work\\\" is the safe default)\\n- Replaces the growth-detection half of Site 3\\n\\n#### Step 3: Refactor `sessionHasNewContentFromLiveTranscript` (Site 3)\\n\\nCurrent logic:\\n```\\nextractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript → (files, ok)\\nif !ok || len(files) == 0 → return false\\ncheck overlap with staged files → return result\\n```\\n\\nNew logic:\\n```\\nif !hasNewTranscriptWork(ctx, state) → return false\\nfiles := resolveFilesTouched(ctx, state)\\nif len(files) == 0 → return false\\ncheck overlap with staged files → return result\\n```\\n\\nThe `!ok` failure case (agent doesn't support transcript analysis, no transcript path, etc.) maps to `hasNewTranscriptWork` returning false — same fail-open behavior.\\n\\n#### Step 4: Delete wrapper functions\\n\\n- `extractFilesFromLiveTranscript` → all callers now use `resolveFilesTouched`\\n- `extractNewModifiedFilesFromLiveTranscript` → replaced by `hasNewTranscriptWork` + `resolveFilesTouched`\\n- `extractModifiedFilesFromLive